-- Brazilian Stock Movers: OGX Petroleo, PDG Realty, Tele Norte
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-01-26T15:51:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/brazilian-stock-movers-ogx-petroleo-pdg-realty-tele-norte.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:45 p.m. local time. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index rose 1.6 percent to 63,511.11, the
highest since July 4.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes  SA (OGXP3 BS) gained 3.2
percent to 16.34 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire Eike Batista was authorized by Brazilian regulators
to export oil, according to a statement in the Official Gazette.  Units of telephone company Telemar Participacoes rose after
announcing the date for a shareholder meeting to vote on a
restructuring plan.  Tele Norte Leste Participacoes SA (TNLP4)  (TNLP4 BS)
gained 3.8 percent to 17.06 reais.  Brasil Telecom SA (BRTO4)  (BRTO4 BS)
added 4.3 percent to 11.25 reais.  Real estate companies gained after Brazilian policy makers
signaled they may cut the benchmark lending rate to below 10
percent.  PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes  (PDGR3
BS),  Brazil â€™s largest homebuilder by revenue, gained 5.5 percent
to 7.48 reais.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS) jumped 5.2 percent to 4.47
reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
